review_blob: Bottle from The Vineyard, Castletown, Isle of Man. Chilled to perfection. Easy pour, clear bronze colour. Caramel notes. Sweet and slightly sticky. Not too bitter.
beer_name: Flying Dog Old Scratch Amber Lager

review_blob: On draft at Stilebridge, Maidstone. The best beer to drag Stella drinkers away from their comfort rubbish. Very interesting aroma, flavour and after taste. Dont be fooled, this is great.
Bottle from Stilebridge, Maidstone. A complete and utter classic beer. My only criticism is slightly too much co2. Sweet and delicious, like a top Belgium beer should be.
Bottle from the fridge at The Stilebridge, near Maidstone. Pours a coudy, but inviting lemon. Sweet delicious hoppy flavour. Keep this one coming.
